The paper deals with the automatic processing and exploration of digitized historical documents, specifically historical newspapers, through document layout analysis and semantic segmentation. The approach combines visual and textual features, which suggests relevance to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The use of deep learning techniques and the investigation of predictive power and generalization capacity also point towards machine learning (cs.LG) and deep learning (cs.DL) sub-categories. Finally, the focus on information extraction from historical documents suggests information retrieval (cs.IR) as a possible sub-category.
